Another name for September is {{nihongo|'''Nagatsuki'''|ながづき}}. The origin of the name is explained in {{ill|September|ja|9月|12=draft|12=draft}}. An alternative name is “Kishū (季秋)”.
In the Eastern lunisolar calendar, because the number of days in a month, known as {{ill|Large and Small|ja|大小|12=draft|12=draft}} (with large months having 30 days and small months 29 days), varies by year, there are years when September ends on the 29th and no September 30th exists.
