{{Lunisolar September}} '''Lunisolar September''' (旧暦九月) is the ninth {{ill|Month (Calendar)|ja|月 (暦)|lt=Month|lt_ja=月|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of the year in the {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Lunisolar calendar|ja|太陰太陽暦|1=Lunisolar calendar|2=ja|3=太陰太陽暦|comment=note that this is not the Japanese lunisolar calendar it is any lunisolar calendar|4=ru|5=Лунно-солнечный календарь|6=de|7=Lunisolarkalender|8=es|9=Calendario lunisolar|10=fr|11=Calendrier luni-solaire|qq=draft|qq=draft}}).
Under definitions preceding the {{ill|Tenpō Calendar|ja|天保暦|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, September is defined as the month that includes {{ill|Frost Descent|ja|霜降|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. In the {{ill|New Calendar|ja|新暦|1=New Calendar (Japan)|lt=New Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, it corresponds approximately to late {{ill|September|ja|9月|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to early {{ill|November|ja|11月|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
Another name for September is {{nihongo|'''Nagatsuki'''|ながづき}}. The origin of the name is explained in {{ill|September|ja|9月|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. An alternative name is “Kishū (季秋)”.
In the Eastern lunisolar calendar, because the number of days in a month, known as {{ill|Large and Small|ja|大小|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (with large months having 30 days and small months 29 days), varies by year, there are years when September ends on the 29th and no September 30th exists.
